properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued February 12 at 6:18PM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS THROUGH THURSDAY WITH ACCUMULATING SNOW
AND BLOWING SNOW ALONG THE SOUTH SHORE...

.Lake effect snow will impact the South Shore through Thursday
morning. Additional accumulations of between two and four inches
are forecast for northern Ashland and Iron counties. Two inches
or less of new snow are expected for the remainder of the South
Shore.

Dangerous wind chills are expected across northeast Minnesota and
northwest Wisconsin as arctic air spreads across the region
through Thursday morning. The coldest wind chills near 45 to 50
below zero will occur from the International border through the
Iron Range and the Cass Lake and Hackensack areas. Wind chills of
25 to 40 below are expected for the remainder of northeast
Minnesota and northwest Wisconsin. Frost bite is possible in as
little as 10 minutes.

* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills. Wind chills as low as 45
below zero.

* WHERE...Southern Lake, Southern Cook, Crow Wing, Northern
Aitkin, South Aitkin and Carlton and South St. Louis Counties.
This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band, the
Grand Portage Reservation and the Mille Lacs Band, East Lake
and, Big Sandy Lake areas.

* WHEN...Until noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST THURSDAY
